def avg_over_images(masked_arr, axis=0):
    return ma.mean(masked_arr, axis=axis)

def med_over_images(masked_arr, axis=0):
    dat = masked_arr.data.copy()
    dat[masked_arr.mask] = np.NaN
    return bn.nanmedian(dat, axis=axis)

def bn_median(masked_array, axis=None):
    data = masked_array.filled(fill_value=np.NaN)
    med = bn.nanmedian(data, axis=axis)
    return np.ma.array(med, mask=np.isnan(med))

In [5]:
for filename in image_list:

    file=CCDData.read(filename,unit='electron')
    header=file.header
    imgtyp=header['imagetyp'].strip()
    imgtime=header['exptime']
    averages=np.mean(file)
    normed=CCDData.divide(file,imgtime)
    if imgtyp in ['Bias Frame', 'BIAS']:
        bias_list.append(file)
        bias_avgs.append(averages)
    if imgtyp in ['Dark Frame','DARK']:
        dark_list.append(normed)
        dark_avgs.append(averages)
        dark_times.append(imgtime)
    if imgtyp in ['Flat Frame','FLAT']:
        flter=header['FILTER']
        flat_list.append(file)
        flat_times.append(imgtime)
        flat_avgs.append(averages)
        if flter in ['sdss_u']:
            flats_u.append(normed)
        if flter in ['sdss_g']:
            flats_g.append(normed)
        if flter in ['sdss_r']:
            flats_r.append(normed)
        if flter in ['sdss_i']:
            flats_i.append(normed)
        if flter in ['sdss_z']:
            flats_z.append(normed)
        if flter in ['halpha']:
            flats_h.append(normed)

u_calibrated = []
for file in image_u:
    exptime = file.header['exptime']*u.second
    sub_bias = ccdproc.subtract_bias(file,master_bias)
    sub_dark = ccdproc.subtract_dark(sub_bias, master_dark, data_exposure=exptime, dark_exposure=1*u.second)
    div_flat = ccdproc.flat_correct(sub_dark, master_flat_u)
    cor_gain = ccdproc.gain_correct(div_flat, gain=gain)
    u_calibrated.append(cor_gain)
    

u_combiner = ccdproc.Combiner(u_calibrated)
u_combiner.sigma_clipping(func=med_over_images)

u_final = u_combiner.median_combine(median_func=bn_median)
mean_u = np.mean(u_final)
med_u = np.median(u_final)
std_u = np.std(u_final)

u_0 = u_calibrated
